-- 
Weidmann, Stark Among Opponents of Bond Buys, Handelsblatt Says

-- B y   J a n a   R a n d o w
-- 
2011-08-09T06:33:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-09/weidmann-stark-among-opponents-of-bond-buys-handelsblatt-says.html
Bundesbank President Jens Weidmann
and European Central Bank Executive Board member Juergen Stark
were among policy makers opposed to reviving the bank’s bond-
purchase program, German newspaper  Handelsblatt  reported,
without saying where it obtained the information.  Weidmann and Stark were joined by Dutch council member
Klaas Knot and a representative of  Luxembourg ’s central bank,
the newspaper reported today. Yves Mersch, governor of
Luxembourg’s central bank, did not attend last week’s meeting,
according to Handelsblatt.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jana Randow in Frankfurt at 
 jrandow@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Craig Stirling at 
 cstirling1@bloomberg.net  